"{\"uid\": \"si.com-college-pennstate-wrestling-aaron-brooks-loses-late-will-wrestle-for-bronze-at-paris-olympics-01j4s568qfrh\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Aaron Brooks, Penn State's four-time NCAA wrestling champion who made a strong run through Thursday's opening rounds of the Paris Olympics, will wrestle for a bronze medal following a last-second loss in the semifinals.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 219, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 5, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aaron_Boone\", \"score\": 0.9999998843209208, \"rank\": 1.1382445323207905e-07, \"text\": \"Aaron\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aaron_Boone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aaron_Boone\"}, {\"begin\": 14, \"end\": 24, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions_wrestling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.3178155390300175e-39, \"text\": \"Penn State\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions_wrestling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions_wrestling\"}, {\"begin\": 37, \"end\": 41, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_I_Wrestling_Championships\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.868381653318194e-13, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_I_Wrestling_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_I_Wrestling_Championships\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brooks fell to fifth-seeded Magomed Ramazanov of Bulgaria, 4-3, giving up a takedown with less than 5 seconds left in the match.\", \"from\": 220, \"to\": 348, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 248, \"end\": 265, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Magomed_Ramazanov\", \"score\": 0.9999998787652731, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Magomed Ramazanov\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Magomed_Ramazanov\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Magomed_Ramazanov\"}, {\"begin\": 269, \"end\": 277, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bulgaria_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9993992578420124, \"rank\": 0.0006011030968924591, \"text\": \"Bulgaria\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bulgaria_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bulgaria_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brooks will wrestle for bronze Friday, seeking to become just the second Penn State wrestler to win an Olympics wrestling medal for Team USA.\", \"from\": 350, \"to\": 491, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 423, \"end\": 433, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions_wrestling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.3178155390300175e-39, \"text\": \"Penn State\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions_wrestling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions_wrestling\"}, {\"begin\": 482, \"end\": 490, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999996393854, \"rank\": 3.578783841599987e-10, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He would join David Taylor, who won gold at the 2020 Tokyo Olympics.\", \"from\": 492, \"to\": 560, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, Brooks appeared poised to follow Taylor's pursuit of gold late into his match against Ramazanov, who made a frantic turn in the waning seconds to surprise Brooks.\", \"from\": 561, \"to\": 732, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Brooks took a 3-0 lead after one period, but Ramazanov scored a takedown midway through the second to cut his deficit to one.\", \"from\": 734, \"to\": 859, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Brooks fended off further scoring after the takedown, forced a stalemate and held his one-point lead until under 10 seconds remained in the bout.\", \"from\": 860, \"to\": 1005, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's when Brooks shot and grabbed an ankle, seeking to prevent Ramazanov from an offensive shot.\", \"from\": 1007, \"to\": 1105, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, Ramazanov spun on Brooks with about 5 seconds left, flipping Brooks in the process for the winning takedown.\", \"from\": 1106, \"to\": 1223, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Brooks will face the winner of the repechage match between Alexander Moore of Canada and Javrail Shapiev of Uzbekistan for a bronze medal at 86 kg.\", \"from\": 1225, \"to\": 1372, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1284, \"end\": 1293, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_the_Great\", \"score\": 0.9999974542607223, \"rank\": 2.125489907839214e-06, \"text\": \"Alexander\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_the_Great\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_the_Great\"}, {\"begin\": 1294, \"end\": 1299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maya_Moore\", \"score\": 0.9999999999236024, \"rank\": 7.636360411800245e-11, \"text\": \"Moore\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maya_Moore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maya_Moore\"}, {\"begin\": 1303, \"end\": 1309, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.9999116276305063, \"rank\": 5.322509972475178e-05, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1314, \"end\": 1329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Javrail_Shapiev\", \"score\": 0.9999999999131433, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Javrail Shapiev\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Javrail_Shapiev\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Javrail_Shapiev\"}, {\"begin\": 1333, \"end\": 1343, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uzbekistan_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9597681494547042, \"rank\": 0.041565069939302236, \"text\": \"Uzbekistan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uzbekistan_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uzbekistan_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The match is scheduled for 1:45 p.m.\", \"from\": 1373, \"to\": 1409, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ET Friday on Peacock.\", \"from\": 1410, \"to\": 1431, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1423, \"end\": 1430, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 0.9999745307005692, \"rank\": 2.5354305159476357e-05, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ramazanov will meet second-seeded Hassan Yazdani of Iran in Friday's gold-medal match.\", \"from\": 1433, \"to\": 1519, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1467, \"end\": 1481, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hassan_Yazdani\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hassan Yazdani\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hassan_Yazdani\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hassan_Yazdani\"}, {\"begin\": 1485, \"end\": 1489, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.999999998236035, \"rank\": 1.7636670853545051e-09, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Taylor defeated Yazdani 4-3 at the 2020 Tokyo Olympics and also bettered Yazdani for world titles in 2022 and '23.\", \"from\": 1520, \"to\": 1634, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Their paths seemed seemed destined for a rematch in Paris until Brooks intervened, sweeping Taylor in a best-of-three series at the 2024 U.S. Olympic Trials in April in State College.\", \"from\": 1635, \"to\": 1818, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1687, \"end\": 1692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999181455, \"rank\": 8.196690817042585e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1804, \"end\": 1817, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions\", \"score\": 0.9999969515280182, \"rank\": 3.042113552565662e-06, \"text\": \"State College\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"RELATED: Penn State's Zain Retherford makes dramatic run to the Olympics  Brooks, the 24-year-old whom NBC Sports called\\\"the new face of American men's wrestling,\\\"began the tournament with two wins Thursday, including one against the overall top seed.\", \"from\": 1820, \"to\": 2071, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1829, \"end\": 1839, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions_wrestling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.3178155390300175e-39, \"text\": \"Penn State\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions_wrestling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions_wrestling\"}, {\"begin\": 1842, \"end\": 1857, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zain_Retherford\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zain Retherford\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zain_Retherford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zain_Retherford\"}, {\"begin\": 1923, \"end\": 1933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 1.938166573925389e-12, \"text\": \"NBC Sports\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 1957, \"end\": 1965, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.5403193837806828, \"rank\": 0.7036270691554867, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brooks defeated top-seeded Azamat Dauletbekov of Kazakhstan 4-3 in the first round of competition.\", \"from\": 2072, \"to\": 2170, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He scored the match's only takedown in defeating the 2024 Asian champion and two-time World bronze medalist.\", \"from\": 2171, \"to\": 2279, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2229, \"end\": 2234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999831784409, \"rank\": 1.6821533728787823e-08, \"text\": \"Asian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a quick turnaround for the quarterfinal,  Brooks dominated No.\", \"from\": 2281, \"to\": 2346, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"8 seed Hayato Ishiguro of Japan in an 11-1 technical fall.\", \"from\": 2347, \"to\": 2405, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2354, \"end\": 2360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hayato_Fujita\", \"score\": 0.9999999975038918, \"rank\": 2.4959853489504335e-09, \"text\": \"Hayato\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hayato_Fujita\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hayato_Fujita\"}, {\"begin\": 2373, \"end\": 2378, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.6749054265129911, \"rank\": 0.266617759045214, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brooks scored five second-period takedowns for the win.\", \"from\": 2406, \"to\": 2461, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He did not allow a takedown in the first two bouts of competition.\", \"from\": 2462, \"to\": 2528, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite winning two age-group world titles anddefeating Taylorat the 2024 U.S. Olympic Wrestling Trials, Brooks went unseeded in the Olympics since he had little senior experience at the international level.\", \"from\": 2530, \"to\": 2737, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, Brooks has compiled a spectacular body of work in NCAA and freestyle wrestling over the past year.\", \"from\": 2738, \"to\": 2845, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2797, \"end\": 2801, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_I_Wrestling_Championships\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.868381653318194e-13, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_I_Wrestling_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_I_Wrestling_Championships\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Hagerstown, Maryland, native won a U23 world title in 2023 before embarking on one of the great seasons in Penn State wrestling history.\", \"from\": 2846, \"to\": 2986, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2850, \"end\": 2870, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hagerstown,_Maryland\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hagerstown, Maryland\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hagerstown,_Maryland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hagerstown,_Maryland\"}, {\"begin\": 2850, \"end\": 2870, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hagerstown,_Maryland\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hagerstown, Maryland\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hagerstown,_Maryland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hagerstown,_Maryland\"}, {\"begin\": 2885, \"end\": 2888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Under-20_athletics\", \"score\": 0.999774688993124, \"rank\": 0.00022531963833966493, \"text\": \"U23\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Under-20_athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Under-20_athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 2957, \"end\": 2967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions_wrestling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.3178155390300175e-39, \"text\": \"Penn State\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions_wrestling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions_wrestling\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brooks went 22-0 on the year with six pins, 11 technical falls and three major decisions.\", \"from\": 2988, \"to\": 3077, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He won 20 of his 22 bouts with bonus points, helping Penn State to Big Ten and NCAA team titles.\", \"from\": 3078, \"to\": 3174, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3157, \"end\": 3161, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_I_Wrestling_Championships\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.868381653318194e-13, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_I_Wrestling_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_I_Wrestling_Championships\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the 2024 NCAA Championships, Brooks went 5-0 with four bonus-point victories to win his fourth national championship and first at 197 pounds.\", \"from\": 3175, \"to\": 3319, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Brooks was named the most dominant wrestler at the Big Ten and NCAA tournaments and won the Hodge Trophy as the nation's most outstanding college wrestler.\", \"from\": 3320, \"to\": 3475, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3383, \"end\": 3387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_I_Wrestling_Championships\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.868381653318194e-13, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_I_Wrestling_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_I_Wrestling_Championships\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only a few weeks after winning the NCAA title, Brooks swept Taylor in a best-of-three final to win the 86 kg freestyle weight class at the U.S. Olympic Wrestling Trials in State College.\", \"from\": 3477, \"to\": 3663, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3512, \"end\": 3516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_I_Wrestling_Championships\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.868381653318194e-13, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_I_Wrestling_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_I_Wrestling_Championships\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Taylor was a three-time world champion in the weight class and the defending Olympic champion.\", \"from\": 3664, \"to\": 3758, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Brooks defeated Taylor 3-1 in the clinching bout of the Olympic Trials, a tour that included abreathtaking late rallyagainst Zahid Valencia.\", \"from\": 3759, \"to\": 3899, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3815, \"end\": 3829, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Olympic_trials_(track_and_field)\", \"score\": 0.8581582794952675, \"rank\": 0.038961038961052005, \"text\": \"Olympic Trials\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Olympic_trials_(track_and_field)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/